  <section class="db-home-section db-agent-cluster" aria-labelledby="clusterTitle">
    <div class="db-home-section__head">
      <p class="db-home-kicker">Not vibe coding</p>
      <h2 id="clusterTitle">An agent cluster for production software work.</h2>
      <p>
        Dreamborn has built an agent cluster that moves software development in
        hours, not quarters. Humans set direction. Agents plan, build, review,
        test, and hand off work through a governed operating layer.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="db-cluster-grid">
      <article>
        <span>01</span>
        <h3>Orchestration</h3>
        <p>Work is decomposed, claimed, sequenced, and handed off across specialized agents.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>02</span>
        <h3>Human in the loop</h3>
        <p>Humans set direction, approve judgment calls, and own risk at the moments that matter.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>03</span>
        <h3>Governance</h3>
        <p>Agents operate inside explicit constraints, authority boundaries, and review rules.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>04</span>
        <h3>Observation</h3>
        <p>Work emits receipts, state, costs, review evidence, and handoff records.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>05</span>
        <h3>Production grade</h3>
        <p>Outputs are tested, reviewed, shipped, and maintained like real software.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="shift" class="db-home-section db-home-section--split" aria-labelledby="shiftTitle">
    <div>
      <p class="db-home-kicker">The world changed</p>
      <h2 id="shiftTitle">Software used to be too expensive to build.</h2>
      <div class="db-inline-queue" aria-label="Old software queue proof">
        <span>Queue evidence</span>
        <strong>Task claimed -> output produced -> review passed -> handoff verified</strong>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="db-home-prose">
      <p>
        You rented software because building it yourself was too slow, too risky,
        and too expensive. SaaS made sense when the alternative was a multi-year
        custom software project.
      </p>
      <p>
        AI has broken the old cost structure. Software can now be designed, built,
        tested, reviewed, and improved with a coordinated system of human judgment
        and AI agents.
      </p>
      <blockquote>What should we own?</blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="db-home-section db-home-compare" aria-labelledby="compareTitle">
    <div class="db-home-section__head">
      <p class="db-home-kicker">The SaaS tradeoff</p>
      <h2 id="compareTitle">Rented software made sense when building was impossible.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="db-compare-grid">
      <article>
        <span>What you give up</span>
        <h3>The rented roadmap</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Your workflow becomes a configuration screen.</li>
          <li>Your best customer insight waits on someone else's sprint.</li>
          <li>Your team pays more each time the tool becomes useful.</li>
          <li>Your operating knowledge gets trapped in a generic product.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>What you get back</span>
        <h3>The owned system</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>The workflow matches how the business actually works.</li>
          <li>The intelligence is trained around your products and customers.</li>
          <li>The system improves when your people learn something new.</li>
          <li>The roadmap belongs to the advantage, not the vendor.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="db-home-quote" aria-label="Dreamborn thesis">
    <p>Rent the commodity.</p>
    <p>Own the advantage.</p>
