  <section class="db-home-section db-home-native" aria-labelledby="nativeTitle">
    <p class="db-home-kicker">AI-native is not a chatbot</p>
    <h2 id="nativeTitle">If intelligence were part of the system from the beginning, how would this work?</h2>
    <div class="db-native-grid">
      <article>
        <span>Bolt-on AI</span>
        <p>A traditional product with search, summaries, recommendations, or an assistant added to the corner.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <span>AI-native</span>
        <p>A system where intelligence sits at the center and the interface, workflows, data, and agents are built around it.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="db-work-loop" aria-label="Dreamborn work queue loop">
      <article><span>01</span><strong>Human direction</strong><p>Goal, constraints, and quality bar are set before work moves.</p></article>
      <article><span>02</span><strong>Agent claim</strong><p>The queue records who took the work and what state it entered.</p></article>
      <article><span>03</span><strong>Evidence produced</strong><p>Outputs, receipts, and review notes travel with the task.</p></article>
      <article><span>04</span><strong>Verified handoff</strong><p>The next step starts only after the system has proof.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

